Sentencas: For solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) applications, there remains a growing interest in developing efficient cathode catalysts.
Titulo: Effect of calcium doping on the electrocatalytic activity of the Bi1-xCaxFeO3-δ oxygen electrode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Herein, iron-based Ca-doped Bi1-xCaxFeO3-delta (BCFx, x = 0.1, 0.2, and 0.3) oxides are evaluated as potential cathode materials for SOFCs.
Titulo: Effect of calcium doping on the electrocatalytic activity of the Bi1-xCaxFeO3-δ oxygen electrode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The phase structure, thermal expansion behavior, electrical conductivity, and electrocatalytic properties for the oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) of the BCFx cathodes are systematically characterized.
Titulo: Effect of calcium doping on the electrocatalytic activity of the Bi1-xCaxFeO3-δ oxygen electrode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Among all compositions, the Bi0.8Ca0.2FeO3-delta (BCF0.2) cathode exhibits the highest oxygen vacancy concentration and considerable electrocatalytic activity, demonstrating the lowest polarization resistance (0.11 omega cm(2)) and largest exchange current density of 41.91 mA
Titulo: Effect of calcium doping on the electrocatalytic activity of the Bi1-xCaxFeO3-δ oxygen electrode for solid oxide fuel cells
Effect of calcium doping on the electrocatalytic activity of the Bi1-xCaxFeO3-δ oxygen electrode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The BCF0.2 cathode-based single cell delivers excellent output performance, yielding a maximum power density of 760 mW cm(-2) 700 degrees C along with exceptional stability over a period of 60 h. This work highlights the Ca-doping strategy for enhancing electrocatalytic activity of the cathode electrocatalysts in SOFCs.
Titulo: Effect of calcium doping on the electrocatalytic activity of the Bi1-xCaxFeO3-δ oxygen electrode for solid oxide fuel cells
